9 “(6) The facilitator may divide the functions of the office into administrative divisions.
10 The facilitator may appoint an individual to administer each division. The administrator of
11 each division serves at the pleasure of the facilitator and is not subject to the provisions of
12 ORS chapter 240. Each individual appointed under this subsection must be well qualified by
13 technical training and experience in the functions to be performed by the individual.
14 “(7) The office shall:
15 “(a) Develop a standardized and expandable training environment for emergency response
16 training in consultation and collaboration with subject matter experts based on strategic,
17 operational and tactical assessments, evaluations and requirements; and
18 “(b) Plan, develop, construct and operate facilities for emergency response training until
19 the facilitator determines that the facilities are fully operational, at which time control of
20 the facilities must be transferred to the Statewide Regional Training Office established under
21 section 18 of this 2026 Act.
22 “SECTION 13. (1) SPARC shall develop and maintain a database to be known as the All-
23 Hazards Statewide Responder Database. The database is to be a centralized and comprehen-
24 sive repository of information regarding individuals and entities with skills or responsibilities
25 relevant to emergency management.
26 “(2) The office shall negotiate any data sharing agreements with public and private enti-
27 ties necessary to develop or maintain the database.
28 “(3) The office shall collaborate, cooperate and coordinate with all appropriate private
29 and public entities with responsibility for the emergency support functions identified by the
30 Federal Emergency Management Agency to develop and maintain the database.
31 “(4) In developing the database, the office shall prioritize the inclusion of formalized
32 emergency response exercise, experience and training information derived from the Emer-
33 gency Management Institute of the Federal Emergency Management Agency, the emergency
34 health care provider registry established under ORS 401.651 to 401.670 and the Department
35 of Public Safety Standards and Training.
36 “(5) The office shall identify, implement and support an appropriate learning management
37 system to be used in conjunction with the database.
38 “(6) The office shall prepare and publish an annual report on the development, mainte-
39 nance and use of the database. The report must include assessments and recommendations
40 for improvement relating to the operation and security of the database.
41 “(7) All agencies of state government, as defined in ORS 174.111, shall assist the office
42 in carrying out the provisions of this section and, to the extent permitted by laws relating
43 to confidentiality, shall furnish information and advice the office considers necessary to
44 carry out those provisions.
45 “SECTION 14. (1) The All-Hazards Statewide Responder Database Oversight Authority is
