15 “FUNDING PROVIDED BY SPARC
16
17 “SECTION 15. (1) SPARC shall distribute moneys, by grant, to develop and operate public
18 safety projects as described in this section.
19 “(2) Before distributing moneys under this section, SPARC shall, in collaboration with
20 the Department of Public Safety Standards and Training and the advisory board convened
21 under section 19 of this 2026 Act, develop construction standards for projects, which may
22 include, without limitation, seismic standards, durability standards and standards for
23 portions of newly constructed buildings that may be used as emergency evacuation facilities.
24 A recipient of grant funding under this section must agree to construct the project in ac-
25 cordance with applicable standards developed by SPARC.
26 “(3) On or before July 1, 2028, SPARC shall make the following grants, subject to sub-
27 section (2) of this section:
28 “(a) $20 million to the Department of Public Safety Standards and Training for a facility
29 in Salem.
30 “(b) $20 million to the Department of Public Safety Standards and Training for a facility
31 to operate, and to train individuals for the operation of, the emergency communications
32 system, as defined in ORS 403.105.
33 “(c) $20 million to the Central Oregon Intergovernmental Council to be used for the
34 CORE3 center in Deschutes County.
35 “(4) In the biennium beginning July 1, 2029, SPARC shall make additional grants for the
36 projects specified in subsection (3) of this section to fund operational costs of the projects.
37 SPARC shall determine the amount of the grants based on the need demonstrated by the
38 projects and legislative budgetary authorization.
39 “(5) On or before July 1, 2031, SPARC shall make two grants of up to $20 million each to
40 recipients, as described in subsection (7) of this section, determined through a competitive
41 process. SPARC shall adopt rules governing the competitive process and shall select recipi-
42 ents so as to maximize the emergency readiness of the state, taking into consideration the
43 severity and types of hazards that may affect various regions of this state. SPARC may not
44 make grants under this subsection for projects that received grants under subsection (3) of
45 this section.
