30 “SECTION 19. (1) The Department of Public Safety Standards and Training shall convene
31 an advisory board to advise the department on emergency resilience strategy. The advisory
32 board may advise on any of the following, without limitation:
33 “(a) Strategic investments and objectives in the short, medium and long term;
34 “(b) Placement and distribution of facilities, equipment and supplies;
35 “(c) Standards for regional training; and
36 “(d) Recommendations for legislative changes associated with statewide emergency
37 resilience.
38 “(2) The department may appoint members to the advisory board as the department
39 deems necessary or convenient. The department shall consider, but is not required to ap-
40 point, the following as advisory board members:
41 “(a) The State Resilience Officer;
42 “(b) The SPARC facilitator;
43 “(c) A member with expertise in capital projects;
44 “(d) A representative of the Oregon Military Department;
45 “(e) A representative of the Department of the State Fire Marshal;
