23 “PROVISIONS RELATED TO THE STATE RESILIENCE OFFICER
24
25 “SECTION 21. (1) The State Resilience Officer shall identify state agencies with respon-
26 sibility for one or more emergency support functions identified by the Federal Emergency
27 Management Agency.
28 “(2) Each state agency identified under subsection (1) of this section shall designate an
29 employee of the state agency as the Emergency Management Responsible Officer. This offi-
30 cer shall act as the primary liaison between the state agency and state authorities related
31 to emergency management, including SPARC and the Oregon Department of Emergency
32 Management.
33 “(3) Each state agency not identified under subsection (1) of this section shall designate
34 an employee of the state agency as the Continuity of Governance Responsible Officer. This
35 officer shall act as the primary liaison between the state agency and SPARTICIS for the
36 purposes of preparing continuity of governance plans.
37 “SECTION 22. Each county shall submit a report to the State Resilience Officer at least
38 once per biennium on the state of the county’s emergency preparedness. The report must
39 include:
40 “(1) An assessment of county-level emergency management administrative support for
41 local first responder agencies and local nonprofit or volunteer organizations associated with
42 emergency management;
43 “(2) An assessment of county-level strengths and weaknesses relating to emergency
44 preparedness, response and recovery;
45 “(3) An assessment of regional partnership development; and
