24 “OREGON DISASTER RECOVERY AUTHORITY
25
26 “SECTION 24. (1) The Oregon Disaster Recovery Authority is established as an advisory
27 group within the Office of the Governor to direct emergency recovery in Oregon. The Gov-
28 ernor shall determine the membership of the authority, subject to subsection (2) of this
29 section.
30 “(2) The Governor shall appoint at least eight individuals to serve as members of the
31 authority from among state agency leadership, local emergency managers and others with
32 expertise in emergency management. The Governor shall seek the advice of the Oregon
33 Homeland Security Council when making appointments to the authority. Members of the
34 authority serve at the pleasure of the Governor.
35 “(3) If the Governor declares a state of emergency under ORS 401.165, the Governor may
36 activate the authority. The authority remains activated until deactivated by order of the
37 Governor. The authority may remain activated notwithstanding the termination of a state
38 of emergency.
39 “(4) When activated, the authority shall:
40 “(a) Coordinate initial crisis services;
41 “(b) Coordinate recovery and mitigation efforts throughout this state, using a framework
42 aligned with emergency support functions as defined by the Federal Emergency Management
43 Agency; and
44 “(c) Coordinate the provision of emergency funding and other aid to local governments
45 or private entities.
HA to HB 4121 Page 9

1 “(5) A majority of the members of the authority constitutes a quorum for the transaction
2 of business.
3 “(6) Official action by the authority requires the approval of a majority of the members
4 of the authority.
5 “(7) The Governor shall appoint one of the members of the authority to serve as chair-
6 person.
7 “(8) The authority shall meet at times and places specified by the call of the Governor
8 or the chairperson. The authority may meet at times when the authority is not activated to
9 maintain readiness in the event of an emergency.
10 “(9) The authority may adopt rules necessary for the operation of the authority.
11 “(10) The Office of the Governor shall provide staff support to the authority.
12 “(11) Members of the authority are not entitled to compensation or reimbursement for
13 expenses and serve as volunteers on the authority.
14 “(12) All agencies of state government, as defined in ORS 174.111, are directed to assist
15 the authority in the performance of the duties of the authority and, to the extent permitted
16 by laws relating to confidentiality, to furnish information and advice the members of the
17 authority consider necessary to perform their duties.
18 “SECTION 25. (1) If the Oregon Disaster Recovery Authority established under section
19 24 of this 2026 Act is activated pursuant to a declaration of emergency, the Governor may
20 hire additional state agency personnel under this section.
21 “(2) Additional personnel hired under this section:
22 “(a) May be placed at any state agency, including the Office of the Governor;
23 “(b) Must perform duties related to the emergency, which may include taking over duties
24 previously performed by other state agency personnel who have been reassigned to
25 emergency-related tasks; and
26 “(c) Must have their employment terminated no later than the date the authority is de-
27 activated under section 24 of this 2026 Act.
28 “(3) Notwithstanding any other law relating to state government employment, additional
29 personnel hired under this section may be recruited and selected through any means the
30 Governor deems appropriate.
31 “(4) The Governor’s hiring authority under this section is subject to the availability of
32 funding. The compensation of additional personnel hired under this section may be paid from
33 the Oregon Disaster Recovery Authority Fund established under section 26 of this 2026 Act.
34 “SECTION 26. The Oregon Disaster Recovery Authority Fund is established in the State
35 Treasury, separate and distinct from the General Fund. The Oregon Disaster Recovery Au-
36 thority Fund consists of moneys appropriated, allocated, deposited or transferred to the fund
