8 “SECTION 28. ORS 401.114 is amended to read:
9 “401.114. The Oregon Department of Emergency Management shall carry out the following
10 functions:
11 “(1) Coordinate emergency management functions on a regional basis within this state;
12 “(2) Coordinate training related to emergency response on a regional basis within this state;
13 [and]
14 “(3) Develop and carry out emergency preparedness exercises on a statewide basis[.];
15 “(4) Oversee collaboration, cooperation and coordination between the state and organ-
16 izations involved in the emergency stockpile plan described in ORS 401.111, the emergency
17 preparedness equipment grant program described in ORS 401.551 and other stockpile or
18 emergency preparedness programs carried out by state agencies;
19 “(5) Take actions as necessary to ensure that supplies, equipment and other materials
20 are appropriately staged in preparation for emergencies; and
21 “(6) Develop and maintain an inventory plan for the sustainable procurement, rotation
